.TH "kernel_accept" 9 "kernel_accept" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
kernel_accept \- accept a connection (kernel space)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" kernel_accept
.BI "(struct socket *sock "  ","
.BI "struct socket **newsock "  ","
.BI "int flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sock" 12
listening socket
.IP "newsock" 12
new connected socket
.IP "flags" 12
flags

\fIflags\fP must be SOCK_CLOEXEC, SOCK_NONBLOCK or 0.
If it fails, \fInewsock\fP is guaranteed to be NULL.
Returns 0 or an error.
